          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2010.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>drained</strong> <strong>cannellini beans</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock</strong>,<strong> BBQ sauce</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and cook for 5-10 min or until thickened to a baked bean consistency – these are your<strong> BBQ beans</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>chives</strong> finely</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2010.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
